## Summary

Implemented suite 19/P02 message rendering:

- **`src/lib/llm/markdownRenderer.ts`** — custom ~250-line React-tree builder for the markdown subset (paragraphs, `*em*`/`**strong**`, inline code, fenced code, `-`/`1.` lists, `[text](url)` links, `[cN]` citation markers as superscript anchors). Headings render as bold paragraphs per spec. All output via `React.createElement` — zero `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.
- **`src/components/llm/Citation.tsx`** — `CitationStrip` + `hrefForChunk` resolver mapping `corpus/projects/<slug>/…`, `corpus/about/…`, `corpus/resume/…` paths to public URLs (returns `null` otherwise so "open source ↗" is omitted). Each `<li>` carries an `id="cite-cN"` matching the inline anchor target.
- **`src/components/llm/Message.tsx`** — `<article data-role>` with `t-meta` header ("you" / "the LLM"), markdown body for assistant, plain `<p>` for user, and conditional citation strip.
- **`src/styles/chat.css`** — added message + markdown + citation styling: mono/`--fg-mute` for user, serif/`--fg` for assistant, `var(--s-6)` between messages, square code blocks on `--bg-mute`, hairline-separated citation footer.
- **`src/lib/llm/markdownRenderer.test.ts`** — 14 tests covering paragraphs, bold/italic, inline + fenced code, lists, links, citations, heading-as-bold, HTML escaping (no script execution), and mixed inline.

Verification: all three required files present; `npx vitest run src/lib/llm/markdownRenderer.test.ts` → 14/14 pass; `tsc --noEmit` clean.

